text.section:
In addition to any other available remedy, a local jurisdiction may institute any appropriate action or proceeding to:
prevent the unlawful construction, alteration, repair, conversion, maintenance, or use of a building, structure, sign, or land in violation of this division or of a local law enacted or regulation adopted under this division;
restrain, correct, or abate the violation;
prevent the occupancy of the building, structure, or land; or
prevent any illegal act, conduct, business, or use in or about the premises.
